  <div class="side-by-side">
    <p class="big">An Adaptable, Iconic Creative Framework</p>
    <p>
      As the tournament evolved, so did the creative vision. Vol. 2 introduced a
      refreshed brand identity that aligned with Fortnite’s evolving seasonal
      themes, showing the Fortnite team that we designed for scale and
      adaptability, working under an accelerated timeline.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="side-by-side">
    <p class="big">Elevating Tfue to Larger-Than-Life Status</p>
    <p>
      By Vol. 3: The Return, the stakes had never been higher. Tfue’s highly
      anticipated comeback wasn’t just a competitive moment—it was a cultural
      event. Driven by a cinematic trailer that turned the tournament into a
      larger-than-life narrative, the final installment matched the debut’s
      record-breaking numbers, proving that esports branding, when done right,
      doesn’t just support an event, but becomes part of its identity.
    </p>
